  <bioghist id="aspace_c256f27a331a45def321a002adff7e04">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Marie Dye received three degrees from the University of Chicago: Bachelor of Science (1914), Master of Science (1917), Doctor of Philosophy (1922). She taught at Michigan State University from 1922 to 1956.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_6062547361d25320da35a5bf537bf7fd">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, reports and photographs used by Marie Dye to write a book titled, "History of the Department of Home Economics, University of Chicago" (1972).</p>  </scopecontent>
